values:
Hey all! (realle just like the 2 people who are actually bored enough to read this, but whatever heh)

   Well it is SUMMER!!! Yippee!! I graduated from Lauralton last Sunday, which was awesome, no more all-girls high school for me!! I am sooo excited for this Summer. I feel like awesome things will happen. Well I do know that I'm going on a BIG vacation to Turks and Caicos in July, which is grrrreat!! I've always wanted to go on an island vacation. I've barely been out of the country (spending a day in Canada while on vacation in VT doesn't realle qualify as an exotic vacation). I can't wait to be in Turks and Caicos!!!!!! :-)  

   So far I've actually been pretty busy for the beginning of the Summer. I've been babysitting a lot for my neighbors. I love taking care of them, especially since the older kids are still in school I get to spend some one-on-one time with just the little ones. I also helped my Mom out with Tricky Tray last week. So much fun, it doesn't even feel like volunteer work, even at 9 in the morning. I remember when I was in elementary school and putting those tickets in the Tricky Tray boxes, so exciting, even though I never won. 

   Today I'm jealous though because I had to babysit Clare Bear while my Mom and Katie got to go swimming at my Aunt's house, in her heated in-ground pool. So they're lounging about having a good 'ol time with my Aunt and older cousins while I'm sweltering in here. I can't even go up to join them now because I have work at four, ughh. Not to mention it's like 90 degrees and we only have fans downstairs, it's too hot to even think. I realle hope that we stay inside for Child Link, because if we go outside I might just die! I only have three more days at Child Link though, which is kind of sad, but that also means I just may survive the horrible Mrs.Dean! :-P

   Alright, I guess that's it for now. I should go upstairs and cool off in my brother's air-conditioned room. Until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/5690.html

Hey, currently having a WONDERFUL time at the Connals house :)  Take my quiz...see how well you realle know me...
http://www.quizyourfriends.com/yourquiz.php?quizname=050223180031-854469

until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/5609.html

Hey, I GOT INTO MERRIMACK COLLEGE!!! Woohooo!  I got into my top choice college, that's where I'm going, and with a scholarship! YAY!! It's awesome, Merrimack's Christmas present to me!! :-)

Well, other then getting into my college nothing realle else new around here.  Monday was a snow day, awesomeness, not to mention that was the day I recieved my acceptance letter, heh.  And Tuesday was a half day, but since my car's locks were frozen I couldn't get into my car to drive to school so my mom let me and Katie stay home, pointless day anyway, 20 min. classes and then a Christmas assembly.  So basically this week is the best, not to mention tomorrow is Christmas Eve!! Yay, can't wait!! And there's less than 48 hours till Christmas, YAY!! And I finally have all my Christmas gifts bought and wrapped, double yay! I LOVE Christmas, it's the most wonderful time of the year!

Well, I better get back to cleaning for our Christmas Eve party.  If I never fold another piece of clothing ever again it'll be too soon!  LOL, well Merry Christmas everyone! Hope you get everything you wished for from Santa, heh.  

Merry Christmas to all and to all a good-night! :-)

Until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/5209.html

Hey all, 
  Well I'm enjoying this second long weekend in a row, woohoo!  And I just go to school tomorrow, and then I have Wednesday off yaaay!! i know, people hate me now, but w/e, heh. 
   Well let's see, this weekend has been pretty good so far, on Friday I watched the Yanks game (they of course won, yay!), then on Saturday I had the SATs, soo fun, only not so much.  Then Saturday night I babysat and watched the Yanks game, which was a grrreat game and I pity all who missed it, the Yankees won!! Good-bye Twins, we're now going on to play the Red Sux, and the rivalry continues!! Then, let's see, yesteday I went pumpkin picking with my family, funess, only my dad kept taking random pictures with his digital camera which made me soo soo mad, but overall a good time had.  Now it's Monday and I just came back from lunch at Mickey D's and getting pumpkin ice cream (yum!) at Sunny Daes, and now I'm here typing, fun fun.  
    Well I think that's all for now, can't wait unti the Yanks-Sox game tomorrow night, followed by no school Wednesday, gunna be great! Until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/4996.html

Yes I know all my adoring fans have been waiting for me to update...or maybe i'm just realle bored and decided to write, ya know w/e.  

Well let's see, i joined this realle kool babysitters community, just a lot of good stuff there.  umm...also ya know been showing up at school and work and i've been babysitting and all same old, same old.  actually i'm doing realle well in all my classes right now, i got a 90 on my first math test!! omg, that was the shock of a lifetime, awesomeness all around.  the only thing about school that's starting to stress me out is this whole college thing, i feel like i'm drowning in deadlines, it's driving me up a wall.  i just wish i could pick the college i wish to attend, and well...just go! why do we have to spend hours going over applications and essays and paperwork and blah blah blah????  ughh, plus i thought my guidance counselor would provide me with well...more guidance than she has, which is getting me nervous, but i'm feeling alittle better as time goes on, hopefully i'll survive!!  well, let's stop talking about college, shall we? heh

Ummm...i've been bize with child link, babysitting and well babysitting as well.  i'm kinda annoyed with 98% of my co-"workers" at work, who actually do nothing and get paid for it, ughh, annoying annoying people.  on the other hand i love going to work, being greeted with all those little smiling faces, my little buddies make it all worth while.  i've also been babysitting a lot, which has been very enjoyable, all the kids i babysit are just awesome.

Anything else...well lets see, i had a long weekend this weekend, in which i spent mostly sleeping, catching up with some friends..oh, and on saturday i definitly spent like 4 hours with my favorite family...the Connals!  it was soooo awesome to see them, i loved hanging out with and talking with them, and playing with all of them, especially Madeleine, she's getting so big!  And i couldn't wait to see my Carolina Bell, oh how i love all the connals, they are just the best.  I wanted to take all seven of them to my house and keep them there, i hated seeing them go.  but i'll see them again at Megan's b-day party at the end of the month, so i'm happy about that, plus we have kept contact through aol and the phone so i get to talk with them a lot :-)

well that's about it for now, i'm prolly writing all this for like no one, lol, but that's alright, i love to write anyway.  Until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/4687.html

Well yea, school has started, that's just depressing and annoying in itself, where did the summer go?  Well, at least I'm a senior now, woohoo go class of '05!  And we actually did get some kool new senior privileges and our senior lounge is incredibly nice, so that part of school is pretty good.  As for my classes..well..they're actually going pretty well right now.  I realle like all of my teachers, and two of my teachers for my electives were my teachers when I was a freshman, so I know and their teaching style and like them both, so that's a plus.  And one of them was my favorite freshman teacher, who is one of the best teachers I ever had, I love the way she teaches and explains things.  She's actually the kind of teacher I wanna be when I become a teacher, so it's great being in here class bc I'm not only learning about Modern Lit, I'm also learning great ways to teach.  
  
  Also, just fyi everyone, my last final is on May 24th..hahaha.  That's right I get out like a month before anyone else, hahaha! (I'm not bragging or anything, not at all)

   Well, let's see, anything else new with me?  Not realle, I started working at Child Link the day after school started, it's kinda rough getting back into the work schedule but I loved seeing all the kids there, I realle did miss them.  It was so great to walk into the cafeteria and have like 5 kids yell my name and come up to hug me, that felt good.  I realle wish we had another long weekend tho, I dont' think I can take school and spending my after-school hours with my boss tomorrow (see I don't mind work, but I don't like my boss at all), so yea, that's gunna be hard.  Umm..I guess that's it for now, ughh I can see the new neighbors across the street jumping into their car, oh how I wish they never moved here, they so do not deserve the Connal house or this neighborhood, ughh ughh ughh.  Anyways, that was my complaint of the day, heh.  Well, until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/4495.html

Hey Everyone,
  Well so it's still summer but those annoying 'back to school' sales are popping up everywhere, you can't avoid the back to school announcements on the radio and stupid commercials on tv.  Ughh, it's all just so depressing, i definitly hate the week before school starts, it just feels like part of my life is fading away, not to return for another year.  Well, ughh, anyway my family and i visited the connals the day before yesterday for Madeleine's first birthday (i can't believe she's already one!), and we had a great time there.  We, of course, stayed the longest with them and it just felt so good to be with them and talk to them and just to spend time with them, i just missed them so much, well it was what i needed. :)  Let's see, i still have to finish my second summer reading book, which isn't tough to do it's just that finishing it means that school will be here soon *gulp*.  My stomach and throat seriously tighten whenever i hear the word school, it's sickening.  Iunno it just feels like when i start school and work and all that it's just a never-ending whirling tunnel in which i wish to escape from, hopefully it won't be as bad as i imagine.  I'm just glad that i didn't have to start as early as seymour, bridgeport and prep (haha!), they all started last week and that's gotta suck.  Anyway, today i decided to make the best of some of the last days of our summer and after going to get my outside senior pics done i brought my little sister to the park down the street for an hour, then we played on her swingset.  After that we had pizza for dinner and then i treated my family to ice cream with my gift certificate, and then we got some movies with my gift cards (putting them to good use), and picked up some soda, good things.  Well i guess i've rambled on enough, i just realle wish that somehow summer could go on forever and the connals could move back across the street, those are my two ultimate wishes, so there lol. well, until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/4322.html

hey there!  yea, haven't updated in like a kagillion minutes (realle less than a month, but w/e i can make up words for it).  let's see...i'm in south carolina right now!! yay for SC, it was realle nice down here today, a great change from the rainy, stormy mess it's been for the past couple of days, so i spent most of the day in the pool, very relaxing.  umm....had a great time in myrtle beach last week, very nice down there the whole time we were there, spent time at the beach (i avoided the ocean of course, lol), and we went out almost every night doing awesome things like shopping, eating out and going to the amusement park.  now we're in a different part of SC at my grandparents' vacation house, very nice here. so, my sister had her birthday then my parents had their anniversary, stef's birthday was a day later (Happy Birthday Stef! the big 1-9!!)...ummm...oh yea and we got another dog, a black lab mix who we named Bella, if ya wanna know how we got her it's a bit of a story so just ask me.  now i'm here typing, i'm bored almost outta my mind, and aol is being a jerk, well what's new?  only acouple peeps are online, and i'm talking to only like two of them and thanking god that this girl who i decided to im but barely know signed off, ya know when you think that a random im will spur a great conversation? well, that didn't happen in my case and i'm now thinking to myself 'what was i thinking, i don't even like that girl'  lol, well i'm too tired to go to sleep right now, realle to do anything which includes thinking and typing lol and i'm hoping that tomorrow will be as nice as today.  uhh...guess that's it for now...reply if you please, heh.  until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/3878.html

Hey everyone.  today and tomorrow are very sad days in my life, my neighbors are finalizing their move (moving trucks, lots of boxes, empty rooms still full of memories, etc.) and it is depressing.  i hate all of it, i realle wish that they didn't have to move, i'd give anything for them to stay across the street, but since there's no way to stop them i guess i'll have to trudge through the move.  it's affecting me more than i expected, and it's very hard to deal.  the only thing that's good in my near future is that my me and my family are leaving for south carolina on thursday, and we're going on a three week vacation there, yay!  that brings up the whole packing situation, or lack there of, though.  i realle rather not sort and pack right now, but at least it keeps me busy and my mind off other things.  and i'm only like half way done packing and we're leaving in two days! eek! that's ok though, i work well under pressure, hey always works well for projects and stuff, like the memory book i made and put together for my neighbors in only two days, which was very tricky.  well, that's about it for now.  i just realle realle hope i'll have a great time in south carolina, and if i don't my life will officially be a total depressing mess, ughh.  but that will certainly not happen, it will not.  ok, well i guess i've babbled on enough. until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/3628.html

Hey, i haven't unpdated in a pretty long time..let's see what's happened since then..well not much (big surprise), let's see, i've been working, hanging out, swimming and playing badminton (soo awesome).  Fourth of July was grreat, played badminton, eat lobster and saw the awesome fireworks, the finale was pretty kool. then when we got home we did some of our own fireworks, a police car went up and down our street acouple times, acouple close calls but we never got caught.  then the connals came home and we got to show them our fireworks and do sparklers and party poppers with them, which was awesome...our last fourth of july as neighbors tho, very saddening 
:-(. well that was it for the fourth.  today my dad had off from work so he took me and katie bowling at nutmeg, wow no personalities for the workers there. and i had to return my bowling shoes twice, once bc of a shoelace malfunction and another time because there was a major rip on the side of one of the shoes, which i could like stick my foot thru, interesting. well, i ended up winning the second game we played there, my score was 117, awesomeness!  then we went to borders and i got one of my summer reading books, and three mystery books, two CSI:Miami book which look awesome, i can't wait to read those three, should be great.  also got the truman show on dvd, which i've been looking for, i could definitly spend like days in borders, it's huge, and their chairs are so comfortable i could read like the whole mystery section there, heh.  well i guess that's it for now, i'm currently helping a fellow yanks fan big sister torture her younger brother who's a red sox fan (BOOOOO)!! it's realle fun tho, heh.  oh, and fyi if i don't feel like talking to anybody or am realle down in the near future it's bc my neighbors who i love to death are moving and i'm very depressed over it, so just work with me.  ok, until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/3360.html

omg i hate livejournal...ughhhhhhh....i just did this huge update and it like erased it, jerkasses.  anyway...alright it's summer and everything is pretty good, cept my car is having a problem and i can't drive it, ughh, oh well i still have my dad's, heh.  i got my report card yesterday, i did well on all my finals cept math, but let's not talk about that, heh.  also i got honors for the 4th quarter, yay! awesomeness, now i can finally breathe easy and fully enjoy my summer (i know it's weird but i can't relax until i find out how i did on finals).  well today was the dress rehearsal for my hip-hop rountine (the recital is on saturday, eek!), but it's a realle fun dance and my sister and sam, jaclyn, kelsey and alyssa are in it so it's a fun group to hang out with.  and we will be doing alotta hanging out on saturday, we have three performances, one at 10, one at 2 and the final one at 6...a whole day with them, hope we survive, lol.  well i guess that's it...i have to get up at 8:30 tomorrow morning to drive katie to school because she's sleeping in and i volunteered to drive her late bc my mom's gunna be working, i wonder how i'll feel about that in the morning...well at least it'll get my up early so i can get a morning frap or something at black rock (a nice breakfast) and it'll get me to start my morning exercise routine which i wanted to start on the first week of summer, one week late isn't that bad, is it? hmmm...let's see then i'm picking up mickey d's and bringing it to megan's school to have lunch with her (how kool is that?).  then i'm going over to babysit from 2-9ish for the best family, the Connals!  the kids are soo awesome, they're the best (there's 5 of them and they're great kids), so i can't wait to babysit them, also to play and hold the youngest, 10 month-old madeleine.  well i guesss that's it for now, mad i can't go to beachfest tomorrow, but i guess that's the way things go.  until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/3001.html

hey everyone, not to brag or anything but...I'M OUT OF SCHOOL!!! IT'S OFFICIALLY SUMMER FOR ME!! HAHA!! sorry for all you poor souls who have like three weeks of torturous schooling left, but there's nothing i can do about it, heh.  Acutally i realle do feel bad for you guys, all the little kids at Child Link are growing restless with another three weeks of school and i feel bad for them. it's like 80 degrees outside and they're stuck in school, it's not right.  and please do remember that i once was stuck in your position and i do feel your pain.  but i have to say being out of school for like the whole month of june is pretty awesome, i can do like anything, it's grrrrreat. anyway, so i went to the blink 182 concert on saturday, which was AWESOME, the best i've been to. you should of gone if you like them, they were all great.  well, i guess that's it for now, hope you all are having fun in school tomorrow while i'm either asleep, at the movies, at starbucks or somewhere else which is 100% more fun than the math, chem or whatever class you're stuck in, heh. well, until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/2688.html

hey everyone, it's me once again.  well i had a grreat weekend, my family and i went on a mini vacation and stayed in a hotel for two days, which was kool cuz i love hotels and we got to swim in the pool there and everything.  also, i got to play a great trick on jaclyn, which was great lol.  memorial day was fun, the rain held off for the parade so i got to see my little sister marching for brownies, soo cute, plus no school which is always a plus.  yea, i should realle be studying for finals right now, which are all this week (chem tomorrow, hip hip horray!), and even though i rather do like ANYTHING else i should realle wrap this up and hit the books.  so yea, 3 more days of finals for me and then i'm done! yipee! then i'm going to the blink 182 concert on saturday (my first day of summer) as well as to a neighborhood hawaiin party, then on sunday i'm going to my cousin's pool party which should be fun.  ok, so i guess i'll go *gulp* study now...until later...

well today's monday, i usually hate mondays with my whole heart and soul but guess what? today isn't just any monday, it's the LAST MONDAY OF MY JUNIOR YEAR!!  yipeee!!! that's right...you may return your jaw to its normal position now.  yep, this was the last monday of classes for my school and since next week is finals but we don't have any finals on memorial day, this is it, the terrible mondays are over as far as my junior year is concerned!! :-) and yea, this was a pretty monday monday, i got a total of two and a half hours of sleep last night, well technically this morning, because i was working on a project i left until the last minute as usual, which i didn't even get to present today, that's just my luck.  but w/e i napped so i wasn't totally exhausted this morning.  the whole school day went by in kind of a haze, i mean i remember walking through the halls traveling from class to class and sitting in my desk, listening to the teacher, but that was about all i remember. it was like my body and mind were disconnected from each other throughout the whole day, but realle who cares it's the last week of school.  oh, fyi shrek 2 is a GREAT movie, saw it on wed. with my little sis, it's awesome, so GO SEE IT all you shrek fans!  well i guess that's it for now, until later...

SCHOOL DAY COUNT DOWN: 4 MORE DAYS!!!!
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/1544.html

hey everyone, not much to update on but i haven't updated in a while so i guess something is better than nothing.  well, let's see...haven't been doing much lately, been driving around a lot in my dad's car since my car still isn't 100%.  i've also been counting down the days i have left in school, 15 MORE DAYS!!! i can't wait until summer, oh how good it will feel to not have anything to do, just swim and drive around, get ice cream, tan (or try to anyway) and la de dah...summer is definitly something to look forward to!! let's see...today's mother's day, happy mother's day to all you mothers!  umm...today was pretty good we went to church this morning where i ran the nursery as usual, only one little boy was there during the whole service, so it was an easy job.  and then me and my sister and my mom went to kohls where i bought an outfit for today, a cute black and pink striped skirt and a black top.  and then we went to the club with the realatives, fun stuff.  well, i guess that's about it for now. until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/1284.html

Hey everyone, guess what? I GOT MY DRIVER'S LICENSE!!! Woohoo!!!! I'm so relieved, i was all hyped up before the test, you would not believe.  Well, the test wasn't at all as bad as i imagined it to be, i only got 1 wrong on the written (it was a stupid question anyway) and i passed the driving part without a flaw, i had Bill which helped bc he is soo nice.  anyways, i got my license yesterday, i actually had to get it done 3 times bc of a stupid signature error, stupid DMV.  And the first time i drive alone is tonight, but not in my car bc my dad needs to bring it somewhere for some parts to get fixed but i do get to drive my dad's car. ok, granted i only get to drive it up the street to the house where i'm babysitting, but hey it's still somewhere.  And who knows where i'll go after i'm done babysitting, maybe to black rock..the mall....rhode island...or down the street to my house, who knows, hehe.  well that's realle all for now, cept i did take the SAT's today, whole bunch of blahness for that experience, fuuuuuuuun. ok well until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/1084.html
hey everyone.  there, i updated so you'll be happy. until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/787.html

hey everyone, it's me yet again.  so nothing realle new goin on around here i did get my icon uploaded, comment if you like that good luck carebear pic.  i also changed the format so the icon would show up, it's so stupid that some formats don't let it, especially since
my favorite format doesn't, ughh, but hey what are ya gunna do?  well today's my brother's birthday, so happy birthday J.P., fun fun...umm....so we're going out to eat tonight, yumm and uh, well that's it for right now. i kno so eventful, but i just felt like i needed to fill the gaping hole of nothingness which was trying to pitifully fill the space following my previous post.  so yea, basically this post is a whole bunch of nothing, bet you're glad that you spent your time reading this.  well ok, until later...
http://luckeduck87.livejournal.com/618.html

hey everyone.  just got my livejournal today after reading Jaclyn's livejournal, yes i am that bored.  it will give me something to do anyway.  well today was pretty good, i had the day off from school, yippee! i saw 13 Going On 30 which was realle good and then i had driving hours from 4-6.  oh and i just got back from an island off of Hilton Head, SC called Dafuskie Island.  it was realle beautiful down there, i went swimming and to the beach where i found tons of realle pretty sand dollars, and i also went horse back riding.  i had a great time down there in 80 degree weather, but unfortunately had to come back to cold, rainy good 'ol CT.  well after driving hours i didn't do much else other than having a "Dominos fiasco", but i am soo looking forward to driving hours and driver's ed tomorrow morning, ony not.  so i guess i'll update later, until then...
